tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ProductionMetrics (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   object_name VARCHAR(255),
   printing_time_minutes INT,
   material_type VARCHAR(50),
   success_rate DECIMAL(5, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE ProductionMetrics (
    object_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    object_name VARCHAR(255),
    production_date DATE,
    material_used VARCHAR(100),
    print_time_hours FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE 3d_printer_metrics (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  object_name VARCHAR(100),
  object_type VARCHAR(50),
  print_volume DECIMAL,
  material_used VARCHAR(50),
  print_time INTERVAL
);

CREATE TABLE printer_inventory (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  printer_model VARCHAR(50),
  printer_location VARCHAR(100),
  purchase_date DATE,
  warranty_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE print_history (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  print_id INT REFERENCES 3d_printer_metrics(id),
  printer_id INT REFERENCES printer_inventory(id),
  print_date TIMESTAMP,
  success BOOLEAN,
  failure_reason TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE ProductionMetrics (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   object_name VARCHAR(255),
   print_time INT,
   filament_weight DECIMAL,
   success BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE PrinterModels (
   model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
   print_speed INT,
   bed_temperature INT,
   nozzle_temperature INT
);

CREATE TABLE ObjectProperties (
   object_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   object_size VARCHAR(255),
   infill_density DECIMAL,
   layer_height DECIMAL,
   material_id INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES MaterialTypes(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ProductionMetrics (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  object_name VARCHAR(255),
  quantity INT,
  print_time TIMESTAMP,
  printer_id INT,
  failure_count INT
)

CREATE TABLE Printer (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  printer_name VARCHAR(255),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  location VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE PrintMaterial (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name VARCHAR(255),
  material_type VARCHAR(255),
  cost_per_kg DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE PrintQuality (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  print_id INT,
  quality_level VARCHAR(50),
  defects_count INT
)

CREATE TABLE PrintOperator (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  operator_name VARCHAR(255),
  experience_years INT,
  operator_type VARCHAR(50)
)
